<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Annotation on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/annotation/</link><description>Recent content in Annotation on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/annotation/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Python SyntaxError — Invalid Type Comment</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/type-comment/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/type-comment/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="syntaxerror--invalid-type-comment"&gt;SyntaxError — Invalid Type Comment&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;SyntaxError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;invalid type comment&amp;rdquo; is raised when a type comment is malformed. Type comments are special comments that provide type annotations for variables and function signatures, typically used with tools like mypy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Type comments are a way to add type information to Python code using comments. They follow the format &lt;code&gt;# type: &amp;lt;type&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; for variables and &lt;code&gt;# type: (&amp;lt;args&amp;gt;) -&amp;gt; &amp;lt;return&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; for functions. Invalid syntax in these comments causes &lt;code&gt;SyntaxError&lt;/code&gt;. Modern Python prefers inline annotations over type comments.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Lifetime Mismatch / Missing Lifetime Specifier — Compiler Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/lifetime-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/lifetime-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="lifetime-mismatch--missing-lifetime-specifier"&gt;Lifetime Mismatch / Missing Lifetime Specifier&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;missing lifetime specifier&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;lifetime mismatch&lt;/code&gt; occurs when the compiler cannot determine how long a reference is valid, or when references with different lifetimes are used in incompatible positions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust requires every reference to have a明确 lifetime that the compiler can verify. Lifetime annotations (&lt;code&gt;'a&lt;/code&gt;) describe the relationship between the lifetimes of references. When the compiler cannot infer lifetimes through its elision rules, or when two references have incompatible lifetimes, it produces these errors.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Missing Lifetime Specifier — Lifetime Annotation Required</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/lifetime-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/lifetime-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="missing-lifetime-specifier--lifetime-annotation-required"&gt;Missing Lifetime Specifier — Lifetime Annotation Required&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A compiler error with the message &amp;ldquo;missing lifetime specifier&amp;rdquo; occurs when the compiler cannot determine which input&amp;rsquo;s lifetime a returned reference should be tied to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lifetimes ensure references never outlive their data. Most of the time the compiler infers lifetimes automatically. It requires explicit annotations when:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A function returns a reference and takes two or more reference parameters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A struct holds a reference without a lifetime parameter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A trait object has ambiguous lifetime bounds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The annotation syntax is &lt;code&gt;'a&lt;/code&gt; — it tells the compiler &amp;ldquo;this reference lives at least as long as &lt;code&gt;'a&lt;/code&gt;.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Missing Lifetime Specifier — Lifetime Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/lifetime/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/lifetime/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="missing-lifetime-specifier--lifetime-error"&gt;Missing Lifetime Specifier — Lifetime Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A compiler error with the message &amp;ldquo;missing lifetime specifier&amp;rdquo; occurs when the Rust compiler cannot determine how long returned references are valid. This typically happens when a function returns references that could come from multiple input arguments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lifetimes are Rust&amp;rsquo;s way of ensuring that references are always valid. Every reference has a lifetime — the scope for which it is valid. Most of the time, lifetimes are inferred automatically. However, when a function returns a reference and the compiler can&amp;rsquo;t determine which input&amp;rsquo;s lifetime it should follow, it requires explicit lifetime annotations.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Swift Error — MKError</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/mapkit-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/mapkit-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="mkerror"&gt;MKError&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;MKError&lt;/code&gt; is thrown by MapKit operations when map loading fails, geocoding encounters issues, or routing requests fail. Common codes include &lt;code&gt;.loadingThrottled&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;.placemarkNotFound&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;.directionsNotFound&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MapKit provides mapping, geocoding, and routing services. &lt;code&gt;MKError&lt;/code&gt; indicates failures in these operations. Unlike many framework errors, MapKit sometimes degrades gracefully rather than throwing, but errors still occur in completion handlers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common patterns:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Geocoding failure&lt;/strong&gt; — invalid or ambiguous address.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No route found&lt;/strong&gt; — impossible route between two points.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rate limiting&lt;/strong&gt; — too many requests in quick succession.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missing entitlement&lt;/strong&gt; — MapKit requires specific capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Geocoding invalid address&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; geocoder = CLGeocoder()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;geocoder.geocodeAddressString(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) { placemarks, error &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// error may be CLError or MKError&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Route not found&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; request = MKDirections.Request()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;request.source = MKMapItem(placemark: MKPlacemark(coordinate: start))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;request.destination = MKMapItem(placemark: MKPlacemark(coordinate: end))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; directions = MKDirections(request: request)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;directions.calculateDirectionsWithCompletion { response, error &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// error may be MKError(.noMatches) or MKError(.loadingThrottled)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Too many requests&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; i &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; request = MKLocalSearch.Request()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; request.naturalLanguageQuery = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;coffee &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;\(&lt;/span&gt;i&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; search = MKLocalSearch(request: request)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; search.start { &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;_&lt;/span&gt;, error &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// MKError.loadingThrottled after too many requests&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: MKMapView without proper setup&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; mapView = MKMapView()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mapView.delegate = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Not setting region or visible map rect&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-handle-mkerror-in-completion-handlers"&gt;Fix 1: Handle MKError in completion handlers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; directions = MKDirections(request: request)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;directions.calculateDirectionsWithCompletion { response, error &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; error = error &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt;? MKError {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;switch&lt;/span&gt; error.code {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; .loadingThrottled:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Too many requests - try again later&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; .placemarkNotFound:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Could not find location&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; .directionsNotFound:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;No route found&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;default&lt;/span&gt;:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;MapKit error: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;\(&lt;/span&gt;error.localizedDescription&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Process response&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-validate-inputs-before-geocoding"&gt;Fix 2: Validate inputs before geocoding&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;geocode&lt;/span&gt;(address: String) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;guard&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;address.trimmingCharacters(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;: .whitespaces).isEmpty &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Empty address&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; geocoder = CLGeocoder()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; geocoder.geocodeAddressString(address) { placemarks, error &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; error = error {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Geocoding failed: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;\(&lt;/span&gt;error.localizedDescription&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Process placemarks&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-rate-limit-mapkit-requests"&gt;Fix 3: Rate-limit MapKit requests&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MapKitThrottler&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; lastRequestTime: Date?
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; minimumInterval: TimeInterval = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1.0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;throttle&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;_&lt;/span&gt; action: @escaping () -&amp;gt; Void) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; now = Date()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; last = lastRequestTime, now.timeIntervalSince(last) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; minimumInterval {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; delay = minimumInterval &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; now.timeIntervalSince(last)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; DispatchQueue.main.asyncAfter(deadline: .now() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; delay, execute: action)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; action()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; lastRequestTime = Date()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-set-up-mkmapview-properly"&gt;Fix 4: Set up MKMapView properly&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; mapView = MKMapView()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mapView.showsUserLocation = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mapView.delegate = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; region = MKCoordinateRegion(center: coordinate,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; latitudinalMeters: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt;,
